						               													<description>Battle Stations: An Operational Game of Modern Seapower&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Battle Stations is a low complexity board wargame of naval conflict concentrating on the operational level. &amp;#10;The game depicts the various areas of potential conflict on a series of maps scaled to about 24 miles to a hex. &amp;#10;The interactions of surface, subsurface, and naval air forces are depicted by silhouette style counters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The data base of &amp;quot;Seapower &amp;amp; the State&amp;quot;, our strategic modern naval game, is used for the unit values, thus providing a degree of mateability between the games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The operational nature of the game is emphasized by five-hour turns and a simple but effective combat system that reflects the lethality of modern weapons systems. &amp;#10;A number of scenarios are provided for likely conflict areas as well as a system to use &amp;quot;Seapower &amp;amp; the State&amp;quot; as a campaign game scenario generator.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
